  "texts": [
    "Our results indicate that public figures' perceived personality can be accurately predicted from their names' location in GPT-3's semantic space.",
    "Our models remained accurate even when controlling for public figures' demographics and overall likability.",
    "Moreover, the models showed high face validity as revealed by the examination of public figures predicted to score at the top/bottom of each of the traits, as well as the personalitydescriptive adjectives occupying the models' extremes.",
    "These findings have multiple implications.",
    "First, they show that LLMs' semantic spaces can be used to study and approximate people's personality perceptions."
  ],
